            <who name="Bron Gondwana">brong@fastmail.fm</who>
            <bug_when>2011-06-08 01:40:56 EDT</bug_when>
            <thetext>Sorry, that&apos;s how IMAP works.  You need to copy first, then expunge.

Your only option is to use the &quot;DELETE PERMANENTLY&quot; option (expunge directly from the mailbox).

Various people have considered a MOVE extension - but until it gets standardised AND supported by clients it won&apos;t be much help for you, sorry.

Marking this WONTFIX - because it&apos;s a fact of how IMAP works.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
